				\begin{document}$${\mathrm{Accuracy}} = \left({\mathrm{TP}}\, +\, {\mathrm{TN}}\right)/\left({\mathrm{TP}}\, +\, {\mathrm{FN}}\, + \,{\mathrm{TN}} \,+ \,{\mathrm{FP}}\right)$$\end{document}Accuracy=TP+TN/TP+FN+TN+FPwhere TP and TN represent the number of patients and controls correctly predicted, respectively; FP represents the number of controls classified as patients and FN represents the number of patients classified as controls.
